		"description": "<p>Through careful development, you have learned to refine the gifts of nature without making them unnatural. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence or Wisdom score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with carpenter&rsquo;s tools and heavy armor.</li>\n<li>You can use druidic rituals to harden wood to the point where it is as durable as metal. The armor&rsquo;s durability depends on your unique blend of magical training and immediately falls to useless scraps and splinters if worn by anyone else. In either case, the armor does not impose penalties to stealth and you have advantage on athletics checks related to swimming due to its buoyancy. You can only have one such suit of armor at a time. The armor absorbs into your new form when you wild shape.\n<ul>\n<li>You can spend 8 hours and 500 gp of ritual materials to make a suit of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.X55hRZyHouQsMs5u]{Medium Armor} with an AC of 14 + Dexterity modifier (maximum 2), and a weight of 10 lbs. The first time you make a suit of armor this way, you gain inspiration.</li>\n<li>You can spend 8 hours and 1000 gp of ritual materials to make a suit of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.dBcMig2h8Dv8AxJm]{Heavy Armor} with an AC of 18 and a weight of 25 lbs. The first time you make a suit of armor this way, you gain inspiration.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.tk8q47k7yjntw4c2]{Fabricate} once between long rests without using a spell slot.</li>\n</ul>",
